Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: 04:24 PM Attorney Ellen Anderson appeared on behalf of the State and Defendant, Axel Garcia Santiago did not appear.    Bench warrant was requested and authorized to be issued on the defendants failure to appear.
Initial appearance on April 19, 2022 at 04:15 pm.

The defendant shall have no contact with L.E.L.R.  of any kind, whether direct or indirect, including in person, in writing, by phone, by e-mail or other electronic means, through a third party or in any other way.   Defendant shall not be in the presence or possession of drugs or drug paraphernalia, or consume any medication or drug except as may be specifically prescribed by a licensed Wisconsin medical professional for defendant, and then shall be taken only as prescribed.    Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol, and not go into places that sell alcohol except incidentally such as a grocery store, convenience store or gas station or other such place where alcohol is not sold for consumption on the premises.  Third party contact with law enforcement one time to make arrangements to retrieve personal belongings.

01:01 PM Attorney Ellen Anderson appeared on behalf of the State and Defendant, Axel Garcia Santiago appeared, pro se by video from Clark County Jail.    Susan Rascon sworn as interpreter appeared by video.    Defendant acknowledged receipt of complaint.    Defendant advised of right to an attorney.  Initial appearance scheduled for April 19, 2022 at 04:15 pm.
